ں—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-09-01-nushell_0_19.mdظ@6857e1f22397ac4cdf44dc5ee4d78dc986e285feb152cb95fba8845cbfc148bb³title: Nushell 0.19‘¬Nushell 0.19عک



Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.19 of Nu. In this version, we fill some long-lived gaps in Nu, improve completions, theming, and much more.
’گگعدTitle: title: Nushell 0.19
Path: Nushell 0.19
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.19 of Nu. In this version, we fill some long-lived gaps in Nu, improve completions, theming, and much more.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-09-01-nushell_0_19.mdظ@9331cab3fe4c0b8bba1ff30f89b0a5a4f298221d135442dde818418cb22087af³title: Nushell 0.19‘¯Where to get itعكNu 0.19 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.19.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want all the goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=extra``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
’گگعTitle: title: Nushell 0.19
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.19 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.19.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want all the goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=extra``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-09-01-nushell_0_19.mdظ@1bcb4c607ba9d79e71a0e2f094f200b4e70c6ac75d3077ffbf2d4c3028acc116³title: Nushell 0.19‘ظ New completion engine (thegedge)عIanimation of Nu completion
Nushell's completion suggestions are now built around the nushell parser. This means completers can now use a much richer context to provide relevant suggestions. This is still a work in progress, but one immediate improvement is that we can now complete commands, flags, and arguments in most nested structures. For example, 
``echo $(l<TAB>``
 will show you all commands that start with l.
The completion work is still very "new", with parts landing in the hours before the release, so please give it a spin and let us know where we can keep improving it.
’گگع”Title: title: Nushell 0.19
Path: New completion engine (thegedge)
Content:
animation of Nu completion
Nushell's completion suggestions are now built around the nushell parser. This means completers can now use a much richer context to provide relevant suggestions. This is still a work in progress, but one immediate improvement is that we can now complete commands, flags, and arguments in most nested structures. For example, 
``echo $(l<TAB>``
 will show you all commands that start with l.
The completion work is still very "new", with parts landing in the hours before the release, so please give it a spin and let us know where we can keep improving it.
—ظVarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2020-09-01-nushell_0_19.mdظ@755285ce5fafc299820f6a38d487a55d182283166b85bdc40975b022f625122b³title: Nushell 0.19‘؛Improved theming (fdncred)عqimage of a Nu table built with hearts
Nu, with love
We're continuing to expand what's possible with Nu's themes, allowing you to configure more areas of how your data is displayed.
image of a Nu table custom colors
You can also configure how the various Nu data types are displayed. You can learn about the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2449] new custom data colors
 if you're interested in configuring them for yourself. There's also and example 
``config.toml``
 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/blob/main/docs/sample_config/config.toml] here
 with an example of how to set the colors you like.
