 now gives back 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2473] simpler columns
 (gillespiecd)
``uniq``
 has 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2472] more examples
 (gillespiecd)
``ls``
 will tolerate more 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2466] OS errors while listing
 (gorogoroumaru)
``cd .``
 now 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2457] does the expected
 (VincentWo)
``math stddev``
 and 
``math variance``
 both received updates (gillespiecd)
List literals can 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2454] now have commas
 (sophiajt)
``str index-of``
 can now do a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2430] reverse find
 (fdncred)
A new 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2429] PowerShell plugin sample
 (fdncred)
New 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2428] ``path dirname``
 and 
``path filestem``
 subcommands
 (fdncred)
The 
``alias``
 command now has 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2418] optional type inference
 (bailey-layzer)
The line editor hinter is 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2405] now configurable
 (amitdev)
``version``
 now includes the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2390] git hash when built locally
 (coolshaurya)
``touch``
 can now take 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2386] multiple arguments
 (jzaefferer)
``date``
 now has 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2383] subcommands
 (gorogoroumaru)
A new 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2381] ``sleep``
 command
 (LhKipp)
Improvements to 
``ls``
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2379] hidden files
 (mattclarke)
``sort-by``
 errors 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2366] now point to mismatched types
 (luccasmmg)
``str``
 subcommands for 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2360] various capitalizations
 (rrichardson)
Time units are now 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2356] more readable
 (mattclarke)
Exit scripts from per-directory environments are now 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2352] run in the original directory
 (samhedin)
We've also got a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/contributor-book/pull/29] Portuguese translation of the contributor book(!!)
 (vpperego)
Improved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/book/pull/126] RHEL installation instructions
 (arnaldo2792)
